WEBVTT

00:00:00.820 --> 00:00:10.630
Alif Laam, Allah, La ilaha illa Huwa Al-Hibb Al-Qayyum

00:00:10.630 --> 00:00:18.130
Nazala alayka Al-Kitaba Bil-Haqq Musabdiqa Al-Lima Bayna Yadihi Wa Anzala Al-Tawrati Wa Al-Injeel

00:00:18.130 --> 00:00:22.230
Min Qablu Hudan Li Al-Nas Wa Anzala Al-Fulqan

00:00:22.230 --> 00:00:27.630
Inna Allatheena Kafoo Bi Ayaat Allahi Lahum Azaabu Shadeed

00:00:27.630 --> 00:00:31.430
Wa Allahu Azizun Yunthu Mtiqan

00:00:31.930 --> 00:00:36.630
Inna Allaha La Yakhfa Alayhi Shajun Fi Al-Ardi Wa La Fassama

00:00:36.630 --> 00:00:40.630
Assalamu Alaikum Wa Rahmatullahi Wa Barakatuh

00:00:40.630 --> 00:00:43.830
Bismillah Al Rahman Al Raheem Al Hamdulillahi Rabbil Alameen

00:00:43.830 --> 00:00:46.830
Wa Salatu Wa Salam Al Ataman Al Akmalani

00:00:46.830 --> 00:00:50.130
Ala Khayri Khalqihi Ajmaeen Wa Baat

00:00:50.130 --> 00:00:58.130
We commence by praising Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala, sending blessings and salutations upon the masterpiece Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:00:58.130 --> 00:01:02.130
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless his entire household and all his companions

00:01:02.130 --> 00:01:10.130
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless all the messengers that he has sent from the beginning of time right to the end

00:01:10.130 --> 00:01:13.030
Where Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was sent

00:01:13.030 --> 00:01:19.430
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us all and make us from amongst those who can learn put into practice

00:01:19.430 --> 00:01:26.530
And convey this deen in a way that it can get to our children and offspring up to the day of Qiyamah

00:01:26.530 --> 00:01:29.430
Beloved brothers and sisters in Islam

00:01:29.430 --> 00:01:32.430
We were looking at the life of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:01:32.430 --> 00:01:37.730
We had got to a point where he had taken part in what was known as Hilful Fudul

00:01:37.730 --> 00:01:46.230
Or the pledge where they had to or they pledged to assist those who were oppressed against the oppressor

00:01:46.230 --> 00:01:54.530
And we also got to the point where he had traveled to Ash-Sham once again to the Syrian region as we call it today

00:01:54.530 --> 00:01:59.330
And as I explained it includes not only the country of Syria but their entire region

00:01:59.330 --> 00:02:03.930
Where Lebanon, Palestine and parts of northern Arabia are included

00:02:03.930 --> 00:02:06.230
So the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:02:06.230 --> 00:02:12.230
It was noticed by Maysara who was the slave of Khadija binti Khuwalid radiallahu anha

00:02:12.230 --> 00:02:17.430
That the cloud was covering him was shading him throughout the journey

00:02:17.430 --> 00:02:19.830
This was something amazing

00:02:19.830 --> 00:02:25.130
Not only was the tree or had the tree turned when earlier in his life

00:02:25.130 --> 00:02:31.530
But the later journey to that region there was always a cloud that covered him and no one besides him

00:02:31.530 --> 00:02:32.830
Subhanallah

00:02:32.830 --> 00:02:37.030
So when Maysara had come back to Khadija binti Khuwalid radiallahu anha

00:02:37.030 --> 00:02:40.830
And she had and she was told about what had happened

00:02:40.830 --> 00:02:46.830
She knew within herself that this man something great something very big about him

00:02:46.930 --> 00:02:51.230
He is about to be a leader or there is something grand about him

00:02:51.230 --> 00:02:56.030
And this was also one of the reasons over and above the character and conduct and honesty

00:02:56.030 --> 00:03:02.630
And so on that we had heard about yesterday that made her propose for the marriage to him

00:03:02.630 --> 00:03:06.930
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us spouses who will be the coolness of our eyes

00:03:06.930 --> 00:03:13.230
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make it easy for all those who are not married to be married to those who will be the coolness of their eyes

00:03:13.230 --> 00:03:15.930
Remember marriage is a very big sacrifice

00:03:15.930 --> 00:03:20.330
People don't realize and understand some people think it's a perpetual honeymoon

00:03:20.330 --> 00:03:22.630
We have a problem with today's generations

00:03:22.630 --> 00:03:28.130
Where the young girls are looking for men who are already wealthy who have everything in life

00:03:28.130 --> 00:03:31.630
And all they need to do is now fit on the man's arm and walk to the mall

00:03:31.630 --> 00:03:33.330
That's what some people think

00:03:33.330 --> 00:03:39.030
But they don't realize those who have had humble beginnings where they have struggled for several years

00:03:39.030 --> 00:03:41.930
Sometimes decades and then come up on their two feet

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:46.630
Sometimes those marriages are much more blessed than hunting for the wealthiest of all

00:03:46.630 --> 00:03:49.630
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:03:49.630 --> 00:03:51.530
The reason I make mention of this

00:03:51.530 --> 00:03:54.530
Look at the choice of Khadija radiallahu anha

00:03:54.530 --> 00:03:56.430
She chose a man orphaned

00:03:56.430 --> 00:04:03.030
She chose a man who basically had nothing besides honesty dignity and that high lofty level of character and conduct

00:04:03.030 --> 00:04:04.330
Subhanallah

00:04:04.330 --> 00:04:11.430
And yet he had never taken part in anything that would have put a mark on his reputation

00:04:11.430 --> 00:04:14.330
Or put a negative mark on his reputation

00:04:14.330 --> 00:04:20.330
We have another very very important incident that occurred when the Prophet salallahu alaihi wasalam was 35 years old

00:04:20.330 --> 00:04:21.930
10 years into his marriage

00:04:21.930 --> 00:04:25.530
We had made mention yesterday of his children and how he lost his sons

00:04:25.530 --> 00:04:31.430
And that his daughters had actually lived and they had seen the day when he was granted prophethood and so on

00:04:31.430 --> 00:04:36.130
But an incident where Quraish found that the Kaaba

00:04:36.130 --> 00:04:39.730
Which is the center of the earth according to us

00:04:39.830 --> 00:04:42.230
The Kaaba in Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:04:42.230 --> 00:04:50.330
Quraish had found that this house was being destroyed or it was run down because of two reasons

00:04:50.330 --> 00:04:55.530
One is there had been some fires that had taken part that had taken place in the past

00:04:55.530 --> 00:04:58.830
And they weakened some of the building

00:04:58.830 --> 00:05:02.030
And thereafter there was some floods

00:05:02.030 --> 00:05:08.030
There were floods that had destroyed some of the walls or part of the walls of the Kaaba

00:05:08.030 --> 00:05:11.430
So Quraish decided we need to rebuild this house

00:05:11.430 --> 00:05:15.430
Now remember the house was built by Ibrahim alayhi salatu wasalam

00:05:15.430 --> 00:05:20.130
There is a narration which states that it was built first by Adam alayhi salatu wasalam

00:05:20.130 --> 00:05:22.330
But that narration is not authentic

00:05:22.330 --> 00:05:27.930
The most authentic narrations point towards the building of the Kaaba by Ibrahim alayhi salam

00:05:27.930 --> 00:05:31.130
And Ismail alayhi salatu wasalam

00:05:31.130 --> 00:05:33.630
And after that it had never been touched

00:05:33.630 --> 00:05:37.330
For your information how it was built at the first time

00:05:37.330 --> 00:05:40.130
No cement nothing to hold the bricks together

00:05:40.130 --> 00:05:44.130
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala had blessed the prophet Ibrahim alayhi salam

00:05:44.130 --> 00:05:47.730
By going down and picking bricks picking little rocks

00:05:47.730 --> 00:05:51.530
And each rock like jigsaw puzzles fitted onto the other

00:05:51.530 --> 00:05:55.830
So the big rocks were actually one above the other with nothing to hold them together

00:05:55.830 --> 00:05:58.330
And yet they lasted generations

00:05:58.330 --> 00:06:01.330
So at this point Quraish decided let's bring it down

00:06:01.330 --> 00:06:04.330
But they were frightened they were scared why the house of Allah

00:06:04.330 --> 00:06:05.730
How can we bring it down?

00:06:05.730 --> 00:06:07.630
This is the house this is the bait

00:06:07.630 --> 00:06:10.430
This is the first house all the people come to it

00:06:10.430 --> 00:06:12.630
All our idols are there everything is there

00:06:12.630 --> 00:06:14.430
How can we destroy this house?

00:06:14.430 --> 00:06:17.730
So al-walid ibn al-mughira who was one of the men of Quraish

00:06:17.730 --> 00:06:19.530
He built the courage plucked it up

00:06:19.530 --> 00:06:22.130
And he said you know what what's our intention?

00:06:22.130 --> 00:06:25.030
Our intention is to rebuild it correctly properly.

00:06:25.030 --> 00:06:28.130
So why should we fear the intention is not to destroy

00:06:28.130 --> 00:06:30.630
It's actually to bring down in order to build

00:06:30.630 --> 00:06:33.030
So he said I will start what's wrong

00:06:33.030 --> 00:06:35.930
And he started and he started destroying a little bit

00:06:35.930 --> 00:06:39.630
And thereafter that evening they all slept and they waited for punishment

00:06:39.630 --> 00:06:41.530
They were wondering what's going to happen

00:06:41.530 --> 00:06:45.330
When nothing came the next day he continued and everybody joined in

00:06:45.330 --> 00:06:49.030
And the different clans were given different parts of the Kaaba

00:06:49.030 --> 00:06:50.630
To bring down and to rebuild

00:06:50.630 --> 00:06:53.630
And amazingly what had happened is they brought it down

00:06:53.630 --> 00:06:56.230
And they started building it the question arises

00:06:56.230 --> 00:06:58.430
How far down did they bring it?

00:06:58.430 --> 00:07:02.830
When they hit a certain point where they saw some green foundation

00:07:02.830 --> 00:07:05.830
Green rock foundation they stopped there

00:07:05.830 --> 00:07:06.830
Amazing

00:07:06.830 --> 00:07:11.730
So the foundation we have today the foundation of Ibrahim a.s.

00:07:11.730 --> 00:07:13.130
And how was it built?

00:07:13.130 --> 00:07:18.030
It was actually built where it had two corners

00:07:18.030 --> 00:07:20.530
And as for the other side it was rounded

00:07:20.530 --> 00:07:24.430
You see what we know as the Hatim today the Hijr Ismail as they call it

00:07:24.430 --> 00:07:26.030
It was part of the Kaaba

00:07:26.030 --> 00:07:28.930
So the two corners one where the Hajar Aswad is

00:07:28.930 --> 00:07:31.930
And the other one where what we know as Rukun Yamani is

00:07:32.030 --> 00:07:36.030
And on the other side it was more like a dome more like a Mihrab

00:07:36.030 --> 00:07:37.630
And what had happened they brought it down

00:07:37.630 --> 00:07:41.530
And they decided that we are going to build this properly

00:07:41.530 --> 00:07:45.530
And in order to build it we are not going to accept wealth

00:07:45.530 --> 00:07:47.130
That is Haram

00:07:47.130 --> 00:07:49.330
So anyone who's got interest money

00:07:49.330 --> 00:07:50.330
We're not accepting it

00:07:50.330 --> 00:07:52.630
Imagine the people of Quraysh knew

00:07:52.630 --> 00:07:55.330
The pagan Arabs knew that interest is oppression

00:07:55.330 --> 00:07:59.430
They knew it why because you milking it out of a poor man

00:07:59.430 --> 00:08:02.630
You milking it out of him and he's actually paying for nothing for time

00:08:02.630 --> 00:08:05.330
In fact may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us

00:08:05.330 --> 00:08:06.630
So they knew that that was wrong

00:08:06.630 --> 00:08:09.130
They said we are not going to accept that type of money here

00:08:09.130 --> 00:08:12.830
No interest and this is made mention of in all the books of Seerah

00:08:12.830 --> 00:08:16.130
The second point they said no wealth of immorality

00:08:16.130 --> 00:08:18.530
Anyone who has earned immoral wealth

00:08:18.530 --> 00:08:20.630
The women who wanted to give money or the men

00:08:20.630 --> 00:08:22.730
If it was immoral we're not accepting it

00:08:22.730 --> 00:08:25.830
And the third type of money they did not accept or wealth

00:08:25.830 --> 00:08:30.730
Was anyone who deceived or conned or cheated anyone out of any money

00:08:30.730 --> 00:08:32.430
Please keep it away. We don't want it

00:08:32.430 --> 00:08:35.530
Believe it or not. They did not come up with so much wealth

00:08:35.530 --> 00:08:36.630
Allahu Akbar

00:08:36.630 --> 00:08:38.230
They came up with just a little bit

00:08:38.230 --> 00:08:41.630
And they started rebuilding the Kaaba

00:08:41.630 --> 00:08:44.730
When they started rebuilding the Kaaba two things happened

00:08:44.730 --> 00:08:47.430
One is they ran out of wealth

00:08:47.430 --> 00:08:50.930
What type of wealth they couldn't build it exactly as it was again

00:08:50.930 --> 00:08:52.630
So they decided what we'll do

00:08:52.630 --> 00:08:55.330
We'll close it as the square or the cube

00:08:55.330 --> 00:08:59.030
And when we get wealth we'll actually complete it at some time

00:08:59.030 --> 00:09:01.130
But there was another problem

00:09:01.130 --> 00:09:04.030
There was the honor of the Hajar Aswad

00:09:04.030 --> 00:09:06.330
This black stone that we know

00:09:06.330 --> 00:09:09.330
The honor of placing it where it is supposed to be

00:09:09.330 --> 00:09:13.030
And all these tribes are arguing who should have the honor

00:09:13.030 --> 00:09:17.630
Remember the argument about Zamzam was solved by Allah Subhanahu wa Ta'ala

00:09:17.630 --> 00:09:20.730
This time Abdul Muttalib was gone

00:09:20.730 --> 00:09:22.730
Abu Talib was there

00:09:22.730 --> 00:09:27.530
The Prophet Sallallahu alaihi wasallam and his uncle Al Abbas ibn Abdul Muttalib

00:09:27.530 --> 00:09:32.630
The two of them took part in putting the bricks of the Kaaba from their clan

00:09:32.630 --> 00:09:35.930
And as this happened and the debate pursued

00:09:35.930 --> 00:09:37.830
The building stopped in some narrations

00:09:37.830 --> 00:09:40.030
Some books of Seerah say for three nights

00:09:40.030 --> 00:09:41.430
There was a debate argument

00:09:41.430 --> 00:09:44.330
They almost went to war as to who must put it

00:09:44.330 --> 00:09:46.030
So that one evening they sat and they said

00:09:46.030 --> 00:09:49.930
Okay, whoever is going to enter the Masjid first

00:09:49.930 --> 00:09:52.130
Whoever is going to enter the Masjid first

00:09:52.130 --> 00:09:56.330
We will make that person the one who's going to judge between us

00:09:56.330 --> 00:10:00.530
As to who is going to place this particular stone in its place

00:10:00.530 --> 00:10:02.430
And who came up with this idea?

00:10:02.430 --> 00:10:04.230
Abu Umayyah ibn al-Mughirah

00:10:04.230 --> 00:10:07.630
He was one of the pagans, one of the leaders of Quraysh

00:10:07.630 --> 00:10:09.930
And he came up with this idea and everybody agreed

00:10:09.930 --> 00:10:12.930
So they didn't tell anyone but they waited

00:10:12.930 --> 00:10:17.030
Lo and behold, Muhammad Sallallahu alaihi wasallam was the first one to walk in

00:10:17.030 --> 00:10:18.430
He hadn't known

00:10:18.430 --> 00:10:20.130
When he came in, they told him

00:10:20.230 --> 00:10:23.430
That look, we are so happy that you walked in

00:10:23.430 --> 00:10:25.730
Al-Ameen, you are the most trustworthy

00:10:25.730 --> 00:10:27.530
You are the one, Subhanallah

00:10:27.530 --> 00:10:32.530
Who has no negative scratch on his slate, Subhanallah

00:10:32.530 --> 00:10:35.030
And you are the one we look up to

00:10:35.030 --> 00:10:36.930
At this stage, remember as we said

00:10:36.930 --> 00:10:39.830
He was quite old, 35 years old

00:10:39.830 --> 00:10:41.830
He had a lot of respect

00:10:41.830 --> 00:10:44.330
And he was not just a pauper from any way

00:10:44.330 --> 00:10:47.030
Now he had had wealth, remember he did business

00:10:47.030 --> 00:10:49.330
And he went up to Syria, Sham

00:10:49.430 --> 00:10:50.530
The region of Sham

00:10:50.530 --> 00:10:52.030
And he came back with the caravans

00:10:52.030 --> 00:10:53.930
And he was an honest upright person

00:10:53.930 --> 00:10:56.030
Lots of baraka in his wealth

00:10:56.030 --> 00:10:59.030
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala blessed him in every single way

00:10:59.030 --> 00:11:00.530
So here they told him

00:11:00.530 --> 00:11:02.230
We need you to resolve the matter

00:11:02.230 --> 00:11:05.530
You tell us who should lay the stone

00:11:05.530 --> 00:11:09.230
So he said okay, give me a piece of cloth

00:11:09.230 --> 00:11:10.930
This had solved the problem, Subhanallah

00:11:10.930 --> 00:11:13.430
They were wondering what is he asking for a piece of cloth for

00:11:13.430 --> 00:11:15.230
They gave him a huge piece of cloth

00:11:15.230 --> 00:11:17.730
And he said every clan

00:11:17.730 --> 00:11:21.630
One representative must catch one part of the cloth

00:11:21.630 --> 00:11:24.530
That corner, this corner, the other one, the other one

00:11:24.530 --> 00:11:27.030
And then he placed the stone in the middle

00:11:27.030 --> 00:11:28.530
And when it was placed in the middle

00:11:28.530 --> 00:11:31.030
They carried it right to its place

00:11:31.030 --> 00:11:32.230
And when it got to its place

00:11:32.230 --> 00:11:34.430
He lifted it with his hands and he put it in place

00:11:34.430 --> 00:11:35.930
Problem solved, Subhanallah

00:11:35.930 --> 00:11:37.530
Big problem solved

00:11:37.530 --> 00:11:40.430
So the honor of placing the stone

00:11:40.430 --> 00:11:42.430
Was Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam's

00:11:42.430 --> 00:11:44.230
Look at Allah's plan

00:11:44.230 --> 00:11:45.930
And yet all the clans were happy

00:11:45.930 --> 00:11:47.330
Because none of them could say

00:11:47.330 --> 00:11:48.630
We did and we did not

00:11:48.630 --> 00:11:49.930
They all took part in it

00:11:49.930 --> 00:11:51.230
And each one of them carried it

00:11:51.230 --> 00:11:52.530
They lifted it, they brought it

00:11:52.530 --> 00:11:54.930
And all he did was put it in its place

00:11:54.930 --> 00:11:58.830
So this was also an amazing rank

00:11:58.830 --> 00:12:00.230
That Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:12:00.230 --> 00:12:02.930
Had given Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:12:02.930 --> 00:12:05.730
And now if you take a look at the Kaaba

00:12:05.730 --> 00:12:07.430
It's important for us to make mention

00:12:07.430 --> 00:12:08.630
Of the building of the Kaaba

00:12:08.630 --> 00:12:10.530
We said the first time it was ever built

00:12:10.530 --> 00:12:13.130
Was at the time of Ibrahim a.s.

00:12:13.130 --> 00:12:15.630
And it had a semi-circular on one side

00:12:15.630 --> 00:12:17.230
The second time was this Quraish

00:12:17.230 --> 00:12:18.330
Time of Quraish

00:12:18.330 --> 00:12:20.630
Where they did not have enough wealth to complete it

00:12:20.630 --> 00:12:22.330
So they had it like a cube

00:12:22.330 --> 00:12:24.530
And they lifted it much higher

00:12:24.530 --> 00:12:27.230
Than it was at the time of Ibrahim a.s.

00:12:27.230 --> 00:12:29.930
They lifted it to eighteen feet high

00:12:29.930 --> 00:12:33.330
And they had six wooden pillars inside

00:12:33.330 --> 00:12:35.730
Which were holding the roof

00:12:35.730 --> 00:12:38.230
So they actually put a roof on it now

00:12:38.230 --> 00:12:41.730
And thereafter it stayed like that

00:12:41.730 --> 00:12:45.130
Until the time of Yazid ibn Muawiyah

00:12:45.130 --> 00:12:48.230
When Abdullah ibn al-Zubair radiallahu anhu

00:12:48.230 --> 00:12:51.030
Built the Kaaba again

00:12:51.030 --> 00:12:53.530
And it had been damaged

00:12:53.530 --> 00:12:55.630
And thereafter when he built it again

00:12:55.630 --> 00:12:56.930
What did he do?

00:12:56.930 --> 00:12:59.830
He built it according to the original building

00:12:59.830 --> 00:13:02.730
Where he added the semi-circular once again

00:13:02.730 --> 00:13:04.830
What Quraish had wanted to do

00:13:04.830 --> 00:13:05.930
And this he did it

00:13:05.930 --> 00:13:08.330
Because at the time of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:08.330 --> 00:13:10.230
Aisha radiallahu anha says

00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:11.830
That he said to her

00:13:11.830 --> 00:13:15.130
That if these people were not freshly ignorant

00:13:15.130 --> 00:13:16.730
They are just coming out from the ignorance

00:13:16.730 --> 00:13:19.330
And they might get excited if we bring the Kaaba down

00:13:19.330 --> 00:13:20.630
Or we tamper with it

00:13:20.630 --> 00:13:24.030
I would have built it according to its original building

00:13:24.030 --> 00:13:26.230
That was built by Ibrahim a.s.

00:13:26.230 --> 00:13:28.730
And I would have put another door on the other side

00:13:28.730 --> 00:13:31.430
So people could get in and out and so on

00:13:31.430 --> 00:13:34.730
So he didn't do it in his lifetime sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:34.730 --> 00:13:35.530
But he said

00:13:35.530 --> 00:13:37.230
What if I were able to do this

00:13:37.230 --> 00:13:39.730
And if the people were not fresh from ignorance

00:13:39.830 --> 00:13:42.030
Remember it was only after the victory of Makkah

00:13:42.030 --> 00:13:44.630
That he would have been able to actually achieve that

00:13:44.630 --> 00:13:45.230
And he said no

00:13:45.230 --> 00:13:48.030
These people might look at it from a different angle

00:13:48.030 --> 00:13:49.630
And therefore we leave it as it is

00:13:49.630 --> 00:13:52.430
So Abdullah ibn al-Zubayr radiallahu anhu

00:13:52.430 --> 00:13:56.530
He had the opportunity later on at the time of Yazid ibn Muawiyah

00:13:56.530 --> 00:13:59.230
When Abdullah ibn al-Zubayr radiallahu anhu was

00:13:59.230 --> 00:14:00.830
Basically the head of Makkah

00:14:00.830 --> 00:14:02.030
The ruler of Makkah

00:14:02.030 --> 00:14:05.130
Some considered him as the Ameer

00:14:05.130 --> 00:14:09.830
And subhanallah he built this in its original form once again

00:14:09.830 --> 00:14:11.030
And thereafter

00:14:11.030 --> 00:14:15.930
It was rebuilt once again at the time of Abdul Malik ibn Marwan

00:14:15.930 --> 00:14:18.530
When again it had been damaged

00:14:18.530 --> 00:14:22.230
And you see what was happening is the floods came in and so on

00:14:22.230 --> 00:14:26.930
What Quraysh did is they lifted the door higher than what it was

00:14:26.930 --> 00:14:28.730
So that water doesn't get in

00:14:28.730 --> 00:14:30.030
So if you see today the Kaaba

00:14:30.030 --> 00:14:31.130
The door is very high

00:14:31.130 --> 00:14:32.830
You can only get up with steps

00:14:32.830 --> 00:14:35.030
Because what was happening initially was

00:14:35.030 --> 00:14:38.930
It was flat the door was on the ground level

00:14:38.930 --> 00:14:41.530
And water would get in and be inside

00:14:41.530 --> 00:14:44.230
So now that they lifted it up the water would not get in

00:14:44.230 --> 00:14:48.130
And up to today there are floods that happen in Makkah in the Mataaf

00:14:48.130 --> 00:14:49.730
But the water does not get into the Kaaba

00:14:49.730 --> 00:14:51.530
Subhanallah up to today

00:14:51.530 --> 00:14:54.930
I have seen a time when the water in the Mataaf was up to my knees

00:14:54.930 --> 00:14:57.030
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:14:57.030 --> 00:14:58.730
Not many years ago

00:14:58.730 --> 00:15:01.530
And subhanallah you find the Kaaba was protected

00:15:01.530 --> 00:15:04.130
In fact now there is something known as a Mizab

00:15:04.130 --> 00:15:06.830
Which they placed right on the roof

00:15:06.830 --> 00:15:10.730
And it is a little gutter from which the water actually comes off the roof

00:15:10.730 --> 00:15:12.230
So it doesn't stay there

00:15:12.230 --> 00:15:15.730
So Abdul Malik Ibn Marwan was the last who rebuilt the Kaaba

00:15:15.730 --> 00:15:17.130
And how did he rebuild it?

00:15:17.130 --> 00:15:21.430
He rebuilt it exactly how Quraysh had rebuilt it

00:15:21.430 --> 00:15:23.330
And this is how it is today

00:15:23.330 --> 00:15:25.630
According to the building of Quraysh

00:15:25.630 --> 00:15:29.630
And for your information what happened lately

00:15:29.630 --> 00:15:33.030
The Saudi Arabian government they did not rebuild the Kaaba

00:15:33.030 --> 00:15:34.730
But all they did is they strengthened it

00:15:34.730 --> 00:15:39.730
So they put a little marble coating outside and inside

00:15:39.730 --> 00:15:41.130
And they strengthened the pillars

00:15:41.130 --> 00:15:44.430
Because these wooden pillars were being eaten by ants

00:15:44.430 --> 00:15:47.730
And they strengthened and reinforced the roof or the ceiling

00:15:47.730 --> 00:15:49.130
Whatever we'd like to call it

00:15:49.130 --> 00:15:51.230
And all they did was they reinforced

00:15:51.230 --> 00:15:53.330
So they did not destroy it and rebuild it

00:15:53.330 --> 00:15:55.530
But they reinforced it

00:15:55.530 --> 00:15:57.330
So this is the history of the Kaaba

